Senior Business Analyst - ERP / Workday (Finance Modules)

Melbourne CBD | 3 - 4 month contract | immediate start |$900 - $1,050 inclusive | Hybrid

About the Company

We've partnered with a leading Australian financial services organisation that's transforming the way it delivers enterprise technology. With a major ERP modernisation program underway, this business is investing heavily in digital capability, process automation, and people. You'll join a collaborative environment that values initiative, partnership, and practical problem-solving.

About the Role

As a Senior Business Analyst, you'll play a key role in shaping and delivering finance-related outcomes across a complex ERP program. You'll work closely with stakeholders from Finance, Technology, and external vendors to define business requirements, streamline processes, and ensure the successful integration of Workday finance modules.

Key Responsibilities

Partner with Finance and Technology teams to elicit, analyse, and document business requirements.

Map current and future-state processes across Finance, Procurement, and Reporting.

Translate business needs into detailed functional and non-functional specifications.

Collaborate with technical teams and vendors during design, configuration, testing, and implementation phases.

Lead workshops and drive consensus across finance, operations, and IT stakeholders.

Support data migration, UAT, and change management activities to ensure smooth adoption.

Contribute to continuous improvement initiatives and ERP capability uplift across the business.

Key Selection Criteria

5+ years' experience as a Business Analyst within large-scale ERP programs.

Experience with Workday (preferred) or other major ERP platforms such as Oracle, SAP, or TechnologyOne.

Candidates with experience implementing any ERP financial modules are strongly encouraged to apply.

Excellent stakeholder engagement and communication skills.

Demonstrated ability to work across complex, fast-paced enterprise environments.

Financial services experience is advantageous but not a pre-requisit

What's in it for You

Join a flagship ERP transformation as part of a wider enterprise transformation

Work alongside top delivery professionals and a supportive leadership team.

Flexible work model with strong work-life balance.

Competitive daily rate and the chance to shape a high-impact program.

About the role


Simplyai' is seeking an experienced Senior Data Engineer to join our growing team. In this full-time position based in Sydney, NSW, you will be responsible for designing, building and maintaining scalable data pipelines and infrastructure on the Snowflake platform. This is a strategic role that will have a significant impact on the company's ability to leverage data insights to drive business decision-making.



What you'll be doing

Design and implement robust, high-performance data pipelines using Snowflake and supporting technologies

Develop and maintain data models, schemas and ETL processes to ensure the integrity, reliability and timeliness of data

Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand business requirements and translate them into technical solutions

Monitor and optimise data infrastructure for performance, security and cost-effectiveness

Provide subject matter expertise and thought leadership on data engineering best practices

Mentor and guide more junior members of the data engineering team





What we're looking for

8+ years of experience as a data engineer or similar technical role

Extensive knowledge of Snowflake/ and its capabilities, including data warehousing, data engineering, and data application development

Proficiency in Oracle PLSQL, Python, and other data engineering tools and frameworks

Experience designing and implementing data pipelines, with a strong understanding of ETL and ELT processes

Familiarity with cloud-based data architectures and data management best practices

Excellent problem-solving, critical thinking, and communication skills

A passion for staying up-to-date with the latest data engineering trends and technologies




We are also looking for people in following Techstack:

1) Snowflake/Data bricks

2) Microsoft Data Fabric

3) Senior Data Modeller








What we offer


At Simplyai', we believe in creating an environment where our employees can thrive. We offer competitive salaries, generous annual leave, and a range of health and wellbeing benefits. You'll also have the opportunity to work on exciting, innovative projects and collaborate with a talented team of data professionals. We're committed to supporting your professional development and helping you reach your full potential.



About us


Simplyai' is a leading provider of AI-powered data solutions. Our mission is to empower organisations to make data-driven decisions that drive business growth and innovation. We're a fast-paced, dynamic company with a strong focus on delivering exceptional results for our clients. If you're passionate about data and want to be part of a team that is shaping the future of the industry, we'd love to hear from you.

Apply now

About the role

We’re a fast-growing electricity retailer based in Melbourne, and we’re looking for an experienced Retail Pricing Manager to take ownership of our pricing strategy and lead the continued evolution of our retail pricing capabilities.

 As a Retail Energy Pricing Manager at our organisation, you will play a key role in driving the company's strategic pricing initiatives and market positioning. In this full-time position based in Melbourne, you will be responsible for analysing market trends, competitor activities, and customer data to develop and implement effective pricing strategies that optimise profitability and maintain a competitive edge.

 What you'll be doing

Manage, Guide, and Teach a small and dynamic Pricing Team

Lead the development, management, and optimisation of retail electricity pricing strategies.

Conduct in-depth market research and analysis to identify pricing opportunities and monitor industry developments

Develop and maintain pricing models to forecast demand, costs, and profitability

Collaborate closely with finance, sales, operations, and marketing teams to deliver pricing outcomes that support business objectives.

Analyse customer data and market intelligence to identify pricing trends and inform pricing decisions

Provide regular reporting and insights to senior management on pricing initiatives and their impact

Stay up-to-date with industry regulations, compliance requirements, and best practices

What we're looking for

Proven experience in a pricing, commercial, or analytical role - ideally within the energy or utilities sector.

Degree in Economics, Finance, or a related quantitative field

Proficiency in data analysis, modelling, and forecasting using tools like Excel, SQL, and Tableau

Strong understanding of the energy market, pricing strategies, and customer behaviour

Excellent problem-solving, critical thinking, and communication skills

Strong leadership qualities and the ability to manage competing priorities in a fast-paced environment.

Proven track record of delivering successful pricing initiatives and driving business impact

What we offer

Our organisation is committed to providing our employees with a supportive and rewarding work environment. In addition to a competitive salary, you will have access to a range of benefits, including:

Be part of a growing, innovative retailer shaping the future of energy in Australia.

Work with a passionate, supportive team that values fresh ideas and continuous improvement.

Opportunities for career development and progression

Flexible working arrangements to support work-life balance

Comprehensive health and wellness programs

Generous leave entitlements and superannuation contributions

Join our dynamic team and contribute to the growth and success of our growing business.

Technology Business Analyst | Oracle Fusion ERP/EPM Implementation

Greenfield Transformation Project | Melbourne, VIC

The opportunity:

Due to significant business growth, Kinetic are currently embarking on a large-scale global transformation program and looking for an experienced ERP Business Analyst with strong experience in Oracle Fusion implementation to help deliver one of our critical workstreams.

This is a fantastic opportunity for someone to join us as we embark on a large-scale greenfield implementation project which will be critical in the continued success and growth of Kinetic

This is an initial fixed term full-time contract for 12 months, however due to the scale of our transformation program this may extend.

Key accountabilities:
Collaborate closely with our implementation vendor partners, championing the Kinetic business and helping to ensure our new ERP is fit for purpose
Work closely with business stakeholders to define and prioritise business needs
Help drive business decisions, and challenge where required. You're expertise will be leant on to inform decisions and therefor outcomes for the Kinetic group
Design and facilitate key workshops and meetings to gather requirements and present findings
Analyse and document business requirements for ERP implementation.
Develop process maps, gap analyses, and impact assessments
Support testing activities and ensure smooth system integration and mobilisation
What you will bring:
A strong background in business analysis within large Oracle Fusion Cloud ERP/EMP implementation projects
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with the ability to improve processes and drive change.
Experience working in complex, multi-vendor environments
Excellent stakeholder management and communication skills, with the ability to bring stakeholders along the journey with ease
Ability to work independently and collaboratively in a dynamic greenfield project environment
Most importantly, our values resonate with you – Passion, Integrity, Respect, Authenticity, Humility
About us:

At Kinetic, we don't just move people - we're creating the positive change our planet needs. As a leader in sustainable transport, we're committed to creating cleaner, safer, and greener environments for generations to come.

Our size and scale give our people real opportunities to learn, grow, and progress in their careers. Calm, positive and respectful team players thrive here. Our people embrace change and are encouraged to stretch their comfort zone while making a difference. We challenge each other to be our best.

We're driven by respect, diversity and genuine connection. From networking groups to community partnerships and volunteering, our camaraderie naturally brings people together. Our energy and dedication keep communities moving and our people growing.

How to apply:

Kinetic is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer and our people represent the community which we service. We invite all suitably qualified applicants to apply, including First Nations People, and people from diverse social, cultural and gender backgrounds.

If you're interested in this rewarding role with Kinetic then click the 'Apply' button now!

Company description:



ATTURRA OPERATIONS PTY LTD



Job description:



What you'll be doing

Atturra is looking for a skilled Power BI Developer for a contract opportunity, to work within our Data & Integration Business, delivering to our Atturra clients in Federal Government, Defence Project.

Atturra is seeking candidates who have a passion for innovative technology and driving customer transformation. This person must be able to communicate with a variety of different audiences and must have strong presentation skills. The ability to work in a cohesive team (Atturra and the client team) is important for this role.

This role is based in Canberra, in our Defence office in Russell on a hybrid arrangement. Additionally, holding an active AGSVA NV1 Clearance is a non-negotiable for this role.

This contract will be until 30 June 2026 with a possibility of a further 12-month extension.

Responsibilities:

Use Microsoft Power BI Desktop Client to author reports
Use Microsoft Visual Studio using RDS to develop tabular models (SSAS Projects)
Use Microsoft SQL Server Management Studio to view database objects
Use GIT tools to sync content from local drive to platform Azure DevOps Repo
Be able to provide information and request new DevOps release pipeline creation, folder and content related security setup including RLS setup post deployment as well as moving/deleting content on Power BI portals.
Data source connections need to be parameterised for SQL Direct query.

Working Conditions:

Hybrid
Canberra
Contract
NV1 Security Clearance a MUST

What will make you successful in this role?

Technical Requirements:

3 + years' of relevant working experience
A bachelor's degree in computer science, information systems, or a related field
Advanced skills in Power BI
Advanced skills in DAX
Advanced skills in SQL and experience with relational databases and database design
Experience with cloud Data Warehouse solutions like Snowflake, Redshift, BigQuery, Azure, etc.
Familiarity with data ingestion tools such as SSIS & ADF
Working knowledge of Cloud-based solutions (AWS, Azure, GCP)
Proficiency in data pipeline and workflow management tools
Strong project management, problem-solving, and organisational skills
Ability to work independently and as part of a team
Ability to guide and oversee the selection and application of data engineering methodologies, tools, and practices
Alignment with Atturra's core values and a commitment to continuous professional development
Focus on client needs, resilience, adaptability, collaborative work ethic, accountability, professionalism, innovative problem-solving skills, and effective communication.

Why is this an exciting opportunity?

Atturra is one of the fastest growing ASX-listed advisory and IT solutions companies in Australia, giving you a strong foundation to fulfil your career ambitions.

We currently have 1100+ professionals working across Australia, New Zealand, Singapore and Hong Kong who are using innovation to lead the way.

This is your chance to make an impact. Come and join our talented and creative team of change makers to redefine the future through technology.

The Data & Integration business unit helps clients unlock the full potential of data by integrating systems and applications, enabling digital transformation through our comprehensive on-premises, hybrid, and cloud integration solutions. We specialise in Boomi, Smartsheet, and OpenText.

What our people say:

"We are working towards a very bright future."

"It's a company with vision and a promising future."

Why you'll love working here

Culture of possibility

At Atturra we embrace innovation within our teams, fostering an environment of possibility and growth. We believe in creating a supportive and welcoming culture, where everyone is encouraged to achieve success through collaboration, continuous learning, and smart work practices.

A strong set of company values

Our culture is reflected by our employees who demonstrate camaraderie, innovation, dedication, respect and excellence in everything they do. These traits have become integral to the way we do business and are the values we strive for.

Valuable employee benefits

Employee benefits, recognition, and wellbeing platform
Career growth via succession planning, internal promotions, and mentorship opportunities
Ongoing investment in professional development through industry and technology certifications, and study assistance
Mental health support through our Employee Assistance Program
Support for family and caring responsibilities, including paid parental leave
Employee referral program, with monetary incentives offered

Commitment to supporting Australia's veterans

Atturra is proud to be recognised as a Veteran Friendly Employer by the Department of Veterans Affairs' Veteran Employment Commitment (VEC) and is committed to supporting Australia's veteran community. We aim to enhance the employment experience for veterans by improving recruitment, support, retention, and leadership opportunities to ensure they have a meaningful and impactful career with us.

What our people say:

"Atturra has a great working environment and management are very supportive of their staff. We celebrate success and have fun while working hard."

How to apply

Careers | Atturra

https://atturra.com/au-en/careers

Recruitment Agencies/Headhunters:

We got this covered. Our Talent Acquisition team is working on our hiring demands and will reach out should we need extra support. Atturra only accepts referrals from agencies on our official supplier list via Agency Portal. Agencies are required to go through our procurement process, have an approved fee agreement, and be invited to participate in hiring for a job opening by the Atturra Talent Acquisition team. Any profiles or referrals submitted outside of this process will be deemed invalid. We request that you do not contact Atturra employees outside of the Talent Acquisition team for any hiring-related queries. To become an official supplier, send an expression of interest via talentacquisition@atturra.com.

Atturra is committed to addressing the digital skills gap and advocating for diversity and inclusion. We encourage applications from all individuals, regardless of Veteran or service status, gender, LGBTQI+ identity, ethnicity, religion, physical ability, or age.

At Hays Enterprise Solutions, our mission is to help organisations thrive by supporting their workforce needs. We partner with over thirty large organisations across Australia and New Zealand providing tailored solutions to ensure our clients have unrivalled access to top talent and unique market insights to build their evolving workforces.

On behalf of our esteemed client, a leading entity in the automotive industry, we are currently seeking candidates for a contract position. This opportunity is available immediately as a contractual role until 31st March 2026, with potential for extension.

The Data Reporting Analyst is primarily responsible for both leading and contributing to the design, development and support of enterprise reporting as well as the supporting the business with self-service reporting capabilities.

Key Responsibilities:

Maintain and update Report Development Standards and related policies and procedures to achieve and maintain best practice in terms of quality, long-term cost and re-use.

Contribute to the design, development and support of Enterprise Reporting in line with Report Development Standards leveraging programming where necessary.

Monitor and Report on performance of Enterprise Reporting against targets and recommends countermeasures where required in order to ensure that agreed objectives can be achieved.

Coordinates and facilitates forums to ensure that reporting and analytics plans, progress and issues are clearly communicated to all business stakeholders and understood and documented in accordance with relevant business processes and business logic.

Qualification / Experience:

Degree qualification in IT or equivalent experience desired.

Experience and applied knowledge of Microsoft Fabric, Power BI and Excel.

5+ years’ accumulative IT industry experience required.

Familiar with industry standard project methodologies and working closely with business users.

Experience in leading mixed-vendor project teams to deliver optimal business outcomes.

Understanding of SAP Business Objects, HANA, Analysis for Office (AFO) technologies.

Proven track record of managing business stakeholders with competing priorities.

Proven budget management experience and financial acumen.

First Australians Capital (FAC) exists to empower Indigenous economic prosperity through a thriving, sustainable, and impactful Indigenous economy. We support First Australians' cultural, creative, and economic strength so that they can become free agents driving their economic futures.

FAC operates under an Indigenous First approach; we ensure that our Indigenous stakeholders are the designers and drivers of our team's activities and decisions.

Position Summary

Whilst this role is advertised for Melbourne, we are open to all other locations if you are the right candidate.

The Impact Measurement & Evaluation (M&E) Lead provides strategic leadership in how FAC measures, evaluates, and communicates its impact. This role ensures we understand the outcomes of our investments and capacity-building, while translating learnings into insights that strengthen the broader sector.

This role has a dual focus:

Internal: Collaborate with other FAC teams to embed a culture of learning, accountability, and continuous improvement across investments and programs.

Internal: The analysis of data and trends to shape strategy.

External: Timely and high-impact reports, submissions and briefing papers to the national and international funding sector, positioning FAC as a leader in impact research and thought leadership to shape how the First Nations funding sector grows and operates.

External: Timely and high-impact reports, submissions and briefing papers to the national and international investment sector, positioning FAC as a leader in impact research, and thought leadership to shape how the investment sector grows and operates.

The Impact Measurement & Evaluation (M&E) Lead will lead the Impact Measurement & Evaluation (M&E) team to deliver academic standard evaluation, research, and communications that support continuous improvement internally and influence policy, practice, and investment externally.

The M&E Lead will manage and mentor two direct reports: the Impact Manager and the Communications & Research Associate, ensuring that impact measurement and communication/storytelling work hand-in-hand.

This role will be hybrid (2 office days), and some state and interstate travel will be required.

Key Responsibilities:

Leadership & Oversight

Lead, mentor, and manage the Impact Manager and the Communications & Research Associate positions.

Promote collaboration with other FAC teams and external stakeholders.

Ensure impact measurement and communications are integrated, amplifying both data and storytelling. Ensuring their work contributes to organisational goals.

Build upon and strengthen existing impact frameworks, tools, processes, and communication models.

Ensure alignment of impact measurement practices with strategy and First Nations worldviews of success and wellbeing.

Monitoring, Evaluation & Learning

Provide strategic oversight of data collection, analysis, and reporting on outcomes across all funds and programs.

Ensure evaluation practices are participatory, culturally grounded, and respectful of First Nations data sovereignty.

Translate findings into actionable recommendations for program improvement and investment decision-making.

Research & Communication

Develop and oversee research outputs (e.g. papers, case studies, and reports) that share insights and influence practice, impact investing, business support, investment, and policy approaches.

Position the organisation as a thought leader in Indigenous-led economic development and impact measurement.

Represent FAC in national and international forums.

Ensure communication reflects Indigenous cultural protocols, truth-telling, and opportunity-focused storytelling.

Sector Influence

Position FAC as a thought leader in Indigenous-led economic development and impact investing.

Share learnings with investors, funders, government, and partners through reports, presentations, and forums.

Stakeholder Engagement

Engage with First Nations businesses, partners, and communities to ensure measurement reflects lived experience and community priorities.

Support transparent communication with investors, funders, and stakeholders about impact outcomes and lessons learned.

Capacity Building

Build internal capability across the organisation to embed impact thinking in strategy, investment, and program design.

Support First Nations businesses in articulating and measuring their impact in culturally relevant ways.

Direct Reports x2

Impact Manager

Communications & Research Associate

Works closely with: Strategy & Performance Lead, Portfolio Manager and external research partners.

Reports to: Managing Director - Partnerships

Key Deliverables:

Develop and manage a high-performing Impact M&E team inclusive of the Impact Manager and Communications & Research Associate, to support and align with organisational priorities, develop resources in the support capacity building of First Nations businesses.

Oversight and refinement of the organisation’s Impact Framework.

Oversight of Regular high quality impact reports to the Board, investors, and stakeholders.

Design and execute research projects (qualitative and quantitative) that analyse trends, challenges, and opportunities in the First Nations economy.

Author high-impact reports, submissions, and briefing papers that establish FAC as a thought leader.

Research outputs that inform sector practice and growth.

Clear feedback loops that integrate learning into strategy and operations.

Translate complex findings into accessible content for diverse audiences, including First Nations businesses, funders, investors, government, community organisations and media.

Represent FAC in forums and stakeholder meetings, presenting evidence-based arguments to inform policy and practice.

Selection Criteria

Essential

Demonstrated leadership experience, with the ability to mentor and manage staff.

Strong track record in designing and leading impact measurement and evaluation in investment, economic development, or social impact contexts.

Ability to translate data and evaluation findings into influential insights for diverse audiences.

Strong research and writing skills with experience producing high-quality outputs for external audiences.

Experience working respectfully with First Nations communities, and commitment to embedding First Nations perspectives, values, and data sovereignty principles.

Strong analytical, strategic, and project management skills.

Desirable

Experience with impact investing, Indigenous economic development, or capacity-building programs.

Experience building organisational capability in impact measurement.

Familiarity with Indigenous Data Sovereignty frameworks.

Key Selection Criteria

Indigenous Business and Community Knowledge – Desirable:

Demonstrated knowledge and understanding of Indigenous communities, cultures, and issues affecting Indigenous Australians in business.

Knowledge of Indigenous economic development and/or impact on the context of capital markets will be highly valued.

Demonstrated leadership and collaboration experience.

Published papers and peer-reviewed journal articles (Journal Articles/Research Papers).

Public speaking and Presentation experience.

Qualifications

Preferred – Postgraduate qualifications in Business Administration, Strategy, Public Policy, Economics or related field (eg MBA, MPP, MComm, MPA or Doctorate)

Bachelor’s degree in a related field.

Experience

3+ years of experience in measurement, research, and evaluation (First Nations sector experience will be highly desirable)

History of working in or with Indigenous organisations, with a deep appreciation of cultural context, community priorities, and economic participation (highly desirable).

Track record contributing to thought leadership, sector positioning, and advocacy.

Board-level reporting and advisory experience, including preparing strategy documents, investment frameworks, or impact reports.

Sound analytical and organisational skills, plus one of the above qualifications or experiences.

Demonstrate ability to lead or contribute to high-performing teams.

Committed to building team capability, including supporting others’ growth through coaching, mentoring, or enabling access to technical expertise and development opportunities.

Ability to align team objectives with broader organisational goals, fostering accountability through clear expectations, regular check-ins, and a focus on continuous improvement.

Financial and Technical Skills

Familiarity with business and portfolio management practices, including monitoring and reporting on performance

Proficient in the use of digital tools and technology platforms.

Project Management

Strong project management skills, including:

Measuring and managing project performance

Adapting to project changes and managing shifting priorities

Meeting deadlines

Managing client, team, and partner expectations

Conducting project reviews

Delivering reports

Continuous optimising project processes.

Additional requirements: 

Ongoing right to work in Australia.

Some attendance at after-hours meetings and/or events may be required.

Interstate travel may, at times, be required to visit businesses.

A current driver’s license.

A national criminal history check (or similar)

To Apply

Please attach a current resume and a 1-page cover letter. Applicants who do not submit these documents will likely not be considered.

About Us

You may not have heard of Bapcor, but you will know our brands. We're Asia Pacific's leading provider of vehicle parts, accessories, equipment, service and solutions and – through our businesses like Burson, Autobarn, Midas, Truckline and Baxters – are inside cars, on four-wheel drives and all over trucks.

In joining our team, you'll be welcomed into a supportive business that spans more than 1,000 locations with over 5,000 team members across Australia, New Zealand and Thailand. We are passionate about our team, with safety and inclusivity at the forefront of everything we do. We're also passionate about our customers, products, and living our values of:

Doing the right thing

Being in it together

Giving a damn

Getting it done




About the Role

We are seeking a Senior IT Business Process Analyst to bridge the gap between our People & Culture function and Technology. In this pivotal role, you'll help shape and deliver People & Culture technology initiatives, ensuring they align with business needs and the broader IT roadmap.

You will be the trusted IT partner for People & Culture stakeholders, helping translate technical solutions into business-friendly outcomes, driving process improvements, and ensuring our HCM systems operate efficiently, securely, and compliantly.

Australian work authorisation is required for this role.

Your Key Responsibilities

Act as the trusted IT partner for People & Culture.

Support and enhance our HCM systems (Oracle HCM, Dayforce, UKG).

Drive process improvements, automation, and data insights.

Lead workshops, gather requirements, and design business-friendly solutions.

Manage system changes, vendor relationships, and project delivery.

Ensure compliance, data governance, and user adoption.

What You'll Bring

Strong stakeholder and communication skills.

7+ years' experience working with HCM or HRIS platforms.

Significant working experience in Oracle HCM ideally supported by HCM certifications.

Ability to translate technical detail into business outcomes.

Experience in process improvement, change management, and data reporting.

A collaborative, proactive approach and passion for improving the employee experience.

Nice to Have

Considerable experience working with Workday, ideally supported by relevant Workday certifications.

Experience in Retail or Wholesale environments.

Why join Bapcor?

At Bapcor, we value our employees and offer a supportive environment for professional growth. You will have the opportunity to make a meaningful impact while working with a dedicated team. Additionally, we offer:

Opportunity to join an Australian owned, ASX listed company and work with an iconic brand.

Asia Pacific's leading provider of vehicle parts, accessories, equipment, service and solutions.

Opportunity to make a genuine impact in a growing organisation.

Potential for career growth and personal development.

Exclusive discounts and benefits across our Burson Auto Parts trade stores as well as our retail stores including Autobarn, Opposite Lock, Midas Australia, and ABS Service Centres.

Industry Leading Paid Parental Leave & Employee Assistance Program.




Bapcor embraces diversity, equity, and inclusion as integral components of our organisational culture. We recognise that diverse perspectives and experiences contribute to innovation and better decision-making, and we strive to provide a recruitment experience that's fair, inclusive, and accessible. We encourage applications from people of all ages, cultures, abilities, backgrounds, sexual orientation and gender identities.




No Recruitment Agencies Please!

While we understand that recruitment agencies would love to offer their support, we kindly request all agencies to refrain from contacting us regarding this job posting. All applications should be submitted directly by candidates.

Take hold of a monster opportunity and join our Finance and Tax team as a Manager - Reporting Enablement.  If you’re a good fit for this role and live in Brisbane, Sydney or Melbourne, we’d love you to apply. 

Why join us?

You'll get 14% super as standard, to help your future come alive.
Unleash your potential and build a career to be proud of through excellent training and development opportunities.
Balance your work between in-person days at our purpose-built hubs and working from home.
In the office, enjoy end of trip facilities, a yoga and multi-faith room, parent and carer rooms, quiet rooms, BrewHub coffee facilities, and collaborative team spaces.

About the role

We’re all about helping our members make the most of their money. And while they go after their goals, you can too. As a Manager - Reporting Enablement, you’ll be responsible for leading the delivery of strategic insights, data enablement, and reporting capabilities across Finance and Tax. You will lead the execution of multiple concurrent projects focused on data, analytics, and automation, ensuring alignment with business priorities and regulatory requirements.

Day to day, you'll:

Lead a high-performing team focused on insights, enablement, and continuous improvement.
Develop and implement data strategies to improve accuracy, accessibility, and usability of financial and tax data.
Drive process excellence across Finance & Tax, including the uplift of reconciliations, workpapers, and documentation workflows.
Support enterprise-wide analytics and reporting requests in collaboration with Finance & Tax leadership.
Assess and implement automation technologies (e.g., RPA, ETL, low-code) to streamline key finance functions.
Design and develop dashboards and reporting tools (e.g., Power BI) for real-time insights and decision-making.
Enhance data governance standards, including data definitions, lineage mapping, and quality assurance.
Collaborate with the Data & AI team to deploy AI use cases (e.g., forecasting, anomaly detection).
Manage relationships with external vendors and internal enablement teams to support delivery.

This role is available as a permanent opportunity. 

While our preference is for the successful candidate to be based in Brisbane, we are equally open to considering applicants located in Sydney or Melbourne.

About you

It goes without saying you'll be a great communicator with top notch interpersonal skills. We'll also expect you to pick up problems and come up with quick, creative ways to solve them. It's quite likely you tick some of the following boxes too:  

Demonstrated experience in leading data and analytics projects within finance or tax functions.
Strong understanding of financial systems (TechOne, Oracle, Workday), data architecture, and reporting tools (PowerBI).
Proven track record in delivering automation initiatives (e.g., RPA, ETL, AI/ML applications).
Experience in managing cross-functional teams and stakeholder relationships.
Knowledge of financial reporting, regulatory compliance, and data governance.
Strong project management skills with the ability to manage multiple priorities.


About us

Our 2.4 million members trust us to take care of over $330 billion in retirement savings. And we help them take charge of their finances and face the future with confidence. Our inclusive culture means you’ll be valued and heard in a respectful workplace. We've created an environment where you can be yourself and do amazing work. It's that simple.

Apply online now

Everyone is welcome to apply. We value diverse thinking, cultures, perspectives, backgrounds, and abilities. Awaken your career at Australian Retirement Trust and apply now. Applications close Friday, 7 November 2025.

We don’t want to leave you with a monstrous wait. So, you’ll hear from us after the closing date to find out whether you’ve made it through to the next round or not. Being fair and up-front is important to us – and recruitment is no different.

Senior Process Analyst - As-Is Discovery

Location: Melbourne CBD (3 Days Onsite Mandate) Engagement: 6-Month Contract Sector: Leading Enterprise Organisation

The Opportunity

Join a major enterprise business in the Melbourne CBD to kickstart a critical operational transformation program. This is a foundational, high-visibility contract role focused exclusively on deep-dive process mapping and analysis. We are seeking a diligent and expert Process Analyst whose immediate remit is to accurately and thoroughly document the current state ("As-Is") of key business processes.

This is a pure analysis role-we need a dedicated expert to establish the baseline before target-state ("To-Be") design begins.

Role Focus: Dedicated As-Is Analysis

You will be responsible for providing the necessary foundation for future design and change. Your responsibilities will center on rigorous documentation and validation:

Process Elicitation: Conduct in-depth workshops, interviews, and observations with business unit leaders and subject matter experts (SMEs) to gather detailed process steps, inputs, outputs, and pain points.

As-Is Documentation: Create clear, standardised, and high-quality process maps (UML, BPMN, or Swimlane diagrams) that accurately reflect how the business currently operates.

Contextual Analysis: Document key process metrics, supporting systems, data dependencies, and existing control points to provide a holistic view of the current operational environment.

Gap Identification: Highlight initial inefficiencies, bottlenecks, redundancies, and control weaknesses within the documented "As-Is" processes.

Stakeholder Validation: Socialise and validate documented processes with stakeholders at all levels to ensure accuracy and consensus on the current state baseline.

Required Skills & Experience

Proven Experience: Demonstrated track record as a Senior Process Analyst managing large-scale, complex "As-Is" documentation projects.

Process Modelling Mastery: Expert proficiency in process mapping methodologies and tools (e.g., BPMN 2.0, Visio, Lucidchart, Aris).

Stakeholder Engagement: Exceptional communication and workshop facilitation skills, with the ability to manage complex, multi-functional stakeholder groups.

Attention to Detail: Meticulous approach to documentation and data gathering, capable of working independently to meet project deadlines.

Hybrid Work Readiness: Must be comfortable working from the Melbourne CBD office 3 days per week to ensure maximum effectiveness in process observation and workshop facilitation.

Job Title: Senior Portfolio Analyst - Portfolio Strategy and Resilience
Salary: Great salary plus 14% super and bonus potential
Ad Text:
Are you passionate about investment strategy and portfolio resilience? Australian Retirement Trust is seeking a Senior Portfolio Analyst to join our Portfolio Strategy and Resilience team. This is your chance to take the next bold step in your career and contribute to something truly impactful. 

 

Why join us?

You'll get 14% super as standard, to help your future come alive.
Unleash your potential and build a career to be proud of through excellent training and development opportunities.
Balance your work between in-person days at our purpose-built hubs and working from home.
In the office, enjoy end of trip facilities, a yoga and multi-faith room, parent and carer rooms, quiet rooms, BrewHub coffee facilities, and collaborative team spaces.

About the role

We’re all about helping our members make the most of their money. And while they go after their goals, you can too. As a Senior Portfolio Analyst - Portfolio Strategy and Resilience you’ll provide complex analysis and research to support the design and integration of asset class portfolios, helping deliver cohesive, total portfolio outcomes for our members.


You’ll work closely with a dynamic team to design investment strategies and decisions aligned with our members’ best financial interests. Your insights will help shape and contribute to our research, identify emerging portfolio risks, and develop mitigation strategies to maintain resilient portfolios.

 

Day to day, you'll:

Undertake complex research and analysis to support the shaping and implementation of portfolio strategy, delivering actionable recommendations.
Share updates and suggestions about risks in investment options and market trends; assist in preparing materials for meetings and committee presentations.
Validate data and methods used in risk analysis before sharing results.
Create clear and accurate risk reports using tools and internal systems, including dashboards for investment performance.
Analyse future scenarios that could impact investments and explore risk mitigation strategies.
Build, maintain, and improve fit-for-purpose data, models, frameworks, and tools for portfolio management.
Develop and deliver timely, complex reports to support negotiations and foster trust with key external partners.

This role is 12-month max-term/ secondment opportunity. 

📍 Location: Brisbane or Sydney.

About you

It goes without saying you'll be a great communicator with top notch interpersonal skills. We'll also expect you to pick up problems and come up with quick, creative ways to solve them. It's quite likely you tick some of the following boxes too:  

You have relevant tertiary qualifications in finance, investments, economics, or a related discipline.
You bring experience in the investment industry or a relevant domain, with strong knowledge of legislation, regulations, market trends, risk-reward optimisation, and emerging issues.
You’re highly skilled in research and analysis, and you’re able to work independently to deliver valuable insights.
Your written and oral communication skills are well-developed, allowing you to clearly share your findings and recommendations.
You excel at stakeholder management and you’re a true team player who collaborates effectively.
You’re proficient in using relevant systems and tools to support your work.
Your attention to detail ensures accuracy and reliability in everything you do.

Apply online now

Everyone is welcome to apply. We value diverse thinking, cultures, perspectives, backgrounds, and abilities. Awaken your career at Australian Retirement Trust and apply now. Applications close COB Wednesday, 5 November 2025. Please include a cover letter with your application.

We don’t want to leave you with a monstrous wait. So, you’ll hear from us after the closing date to find out whether you’ve made it through to the next round or not. Being fair and up-front is important to us – and recruitment is no different.

Job Title: Lead Data Engineer – AWS / Big Data / Cloud Transformation
Ad Text:
Join a high-performing Data team that’s driving a large-scale transformation program within the banking and financial services industry. This is an excellent opportunity for an ambitious and technically strong Data Engineer to play a lead role in shaping a modern, cloud-based data platform.

You’ll be joining a collaborative, forward-thinking environment where innovation, problem-solving, and technology excellence are at the heart of everything they do.

What you’ll be doing As a Lead Data Engineer, you’ll take ownership of major data initiatives, leading a team to modernise and optimise core data pipelines and platforms. You’ll combine strategic thinking with hands-on expertise to deliver scalable, automated, and efficient data solutions leveraging cloud and big data technologies.

Key responsibilities
Lead the design and delivery of end-to-end data engineering solutions across key transformation programs.
Guide and mentor a team of engineers to build efficient, high-quality data pipelines and integrations.
Drive platform optimisation through automation and AI capabilities.
Collaborate with architects, analysts, and business stakeholders to align solutions with strategic data objectives.
What you’ll bring
Deep Big Data and Hadoop experience with strong Spark, Hive, and Presto (or equivalent) skills.
Expert-level SQL, including query tuning and optimisation.
Proven experience implementing ETL/ELT solutions using tools like Talend, DataStage, or Informatica.
Strong AWS experience across EC2, S3, RDS, and EMR.
Sound understanding of data modelling, metadata management, lineage, and data quality frameworks.
Hands-on Python experience, particularly in automation and AI integration.
Why apply You’ll be part of an organisation that values collaboration, innovation, and technical excellence. This is a key leadership opportunity for someone passionate about modern data engineering, automation, and cloud transformation within a leading financial institution.

Guidewire Claims Center Program. Financial Services Client. Competitive Rate. 12 month initial contract.

Your new company

Join a leading consultancy supporting a reputable insurance organisation embarking on a major cloud upgrade of their Guidewire Claims Center platform. With confirmed funding and a strong delivery roadmap, this organisation is scaling up its business analysis and engineering capability to support a multi-year transformation.

Your new role


As a Business Analyst, you'll play a key role in the Guidewire upgrade project, specifically focused on Claims Center (not Policy or Billing). You'll work across integration capability, data migration, and system understanding, contributing to a technically functional team during the discovery phase and beyond.


Your Responsibilities

Collaborate with engineers and stakeholders to support the upgrade of Guidewire Claims Center to cloud
Analyse and document integration and data migration requirements
Work closely with vendors and internal teams to ensure alignment across deliverables
Provide insights into system functionality and support testing and validation activities
Attend onsite meetings with delivery partners and internal stakeholders as required

What you'll need to succeed


Minimum 2 years of recent experience (within the last 3 years) as a Business Analyst on Guidewire Claims Center projects
Strong understanding of integration and data migration in insurance platforms
Technofunctional skillset with the ability to bridge business and technical teams
Excellent stakeholder engagement and documentation skills
Able to go into Sydney based office 3 days per week

What you'll get in return

Competitive rate, long term contract, hybrid working.

Drive cutting-edge data platform development / Shape university-wide analytics capabilities / Lead cloud-based data innovation
Apply now to spearhead data engineering excellence and transform analytics capabilities at a world-class university
Investing in you - benefits package including salary packaging, health and wellbeing programs, discounted services, and professional development opportunities.


The University of Melbourne
We take pride in our people, who all contribute to our mission to benefit society through the transformative impact of education and research. Discover more via our website.

Your next career opportunity
As the Data Engineering and Analytics Manager at the University of Melbourne, you'll play a pivotal role in shaping the institution's data future. You'll lead the development and support of the Enterprise Data Lake (AWS) and Enterprise Data Warehouse (EDW) platforms, turning data models into robust operational outcomes that enable enterprise reporting and analytics. This role offers you the opportunity to drive innovation in cloud-based data solutions, lead a high-performing team, and directly impact the university's data-driven decision-making capabilities.

Your responsibilities will include:

Platform Leadership: Provide direction and oversight for the Snowflake data warehouse and AWS data lake architecture, ensuring alignment with organisational goals.

Team Management: Lead and develop a team of data engineers and analytical analysts, fostering a high-performing, collaborative culture.

Data Pipeline Development: Oversee the creation of scalable, secure data pipelines, ensuring efficient data movement, transformation, and governance.

Innovation: Drive the evolution of data engineering and data science practices, embedding best practices in automation, security, and performance.

You may be a great fit if:
You are an experienced data leader with a strong technical background in data engineering and warehousing, possessing excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to drive innovation in complex, enterprise-scale data environments.

You may also:

Hold a Bachelor's or Post Graduate degree in Information Technology, Computer Science, or a related field.

Have proven leadership experience in managing data engineering and data science teams, preferably in AWS or Snowflake environments.

Demonstrate deep understanding of data governance, security, and compliance in cloud environments.

Possess strong communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to engage effectively with diverse stakeholders.

Show a commitment to mentoring and developing team members, fostering a culture of continuous learning and innovation.


For further information please refer to the attached PD.

What we offer you!
We offer the opportunity to be part of a vibrant community and enjoy a comprehensive range of benefits to support your success and sense of fulfilment, including:

Supportive flexible work arrangements underpinned by our commitment to inclusion and well-being
Progressive, considerate leave provisions to empower your work-life balance
Salary packaging and access to a range of discounted services including Bupa health insurance
Health and well-being services including a leading Employee Assistance Program


For more information check out our benefits page!
